This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it proposes a novel image captioning model that incorporates facial expression features to generate more expressive and correlated image captions. The paper also uses long short-term memory networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed models using standard evaluation metrics, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
